						               													<description>Vorbereitung zur Walpurgisnacht is the first of a trilogy of witchcraft games from the Japanese coterie circle &amp;#225;&amp;#154;&amp;#171; &amp;#225;&amp;#154;&amp;#177; &amp;#225;&amp;#155;&amp;#143; &amp;#225;&amp;#155;&amp;#150; &amp;#225;&amp;#155;&amp;#151; &amp;#225;&amp;#155;&amp;#129; &amp;#225;&amp;#155;&amp;#139; &amp;#225;&amp;#155;&amp;#129; &amp;#225;&amp;#154;&amp;#171; (Artemisia). The game is for three players only, and has the three witches concocting their flying potions, to be used in the successive game Brocken, when they fly for Walpurgisnacht.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The original game has a trifold game board of thick card, with different sections to complete the potions. There is a large deck of cards for the ingredients (frogs, Nightshade, Wormwood and so on). There are also some coloured minerals used as markers, and the game was delivered in a cloth pouch.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The later edition is boxed and upgraded to a wooden board and a d4 die is added, along with an ingredients card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players use the cards from their hand to collect the ingredients and brew their potion. The first witch to succeed wins the game and takes flight to Brocken...&amp;#10;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
